                            <comment id="15756144" author="stulac" created="Sat, 17 Dec 2016 02:47:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch file I used to fix and test the fix on fixes-2.7.x-fixes branch. I also created a pull request with this fix as &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/216&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/216&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15761989" author="stulac" created="Mon, 19 Dec 2016 18:54:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching my model of Aegis Data Binding, as it pertains to this defect.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15764113" author="dkulp" created="Tue, 20 Dec 2016 12:37:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Out of curiosity:  if you have a schema for the data, why are you using Aegis instead of JAXB?  Aegis is really just for &quot;java first&quot; cases.  It&apos;s not designed to support the full set of JAXB annotations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15765105" author="stulac" created="Tue, 20 Dec 2016 19:58:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re using Aegis primarily for historical reasons - development of CodeObjects &quot;model-driven&quot; application-development platform started back in 2006 when CXF was XFire and (AFAIK) JAXB was not yet a viable option. We have customized serialization of  SDO-based data, so moving to JAXB data binding would require unknown amount of work and has significant risks associated with it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it does seem at this point as if we&apos;d be better off switching to JAXB databinding, especially for this particular use case, where we need to implement against 3rd party XML schema.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
